'''The Guys''' is a [[2002]] play by [[Ann Nelson (journalist)|Ann Nelson]] about the effects of the [[9/11]] events as viewed from the eyes of Joan, a reporter who is tasked with writing obituaries for fallen firefighters.  It presented in the form of a dialogue between Joan and the surviving FDNY captain, Nick<ref name="CultureVulture" >{{cite web| date = [[May 22]] [[2003]] | url = http://www.culturevulture.net/Theater5/Guys.htm | title = The Guys| publisher =Culture Vulture | accessdate =2006-10-01}}</ref>.  The play debuted [[off-Broadway]] at [[The Flea Theater]], and enjoyed a commemorative rerun in 2006 on the 5th anniversary of 9/11.  In the movie version and parts of the theatrical run Joan is played by [[Sigourney Weaver]], who was nominated for a [[International Press Academy|Golden Satellite Award]] for best performance by an actress for her role.

